frameDefinitions: This frame describes a Sufferer who experiences the loss of someone through death.
This frame is concerned with the likelihood of a Hypothetical_event occurring.
A Communicator conveys a Message to an Addressee; the Topic and Medium of the communication also may be expressed.
Some Content is part of the mental model of a Cognizer.
A Cognizer has a piece of Content in their model of the world.
A person (Speaker) expresses a Message or mental content, broadly understood, in a particular Manner.
frameExamples: She <t>lost</t> her husband in the war.
It is <t>likely</t> that he'll arrive late.
Let's hope it did n't have time to <t>communicate</t> any of its findings to its overlords.
Your boss is <t>aware</t> of your commitment.
listRoleDefinitions: The being or entity that emotionally experiences the death of the <fen>Deceased</fen>.
The entity that has died.
The <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Deceased</fen> passed away.
The <fen>Place</fen> where the <fen>Deceased</fen> passed away.
The state of affairs or occurrence whose likelihood is assessed.
When the event occurs.
Where the event takes place.
The sentient entity that uses language in the written or spoken modality to convey a <fen>Message</fen> to the <fen>Addressee</fen>.
<fen>Message</fen> is a proposition or set of propositions that the <fen>Communicator</fen> wants the <fen>Addressee</fen> to believe or take for granted.
The <fen>Topic</fen> is the subject matter to which the <fen>Message</fen> pertains. It is normally expressed as a PP Complement headed by 'about', but in some cases it can appear as a direct object.
The physical or abstract setting in which the <fen>Message</fen> is conveyed.
The time at which the communication takes place.
The location where the act of communication occurs.
The fact or idea which the <fen>Cognizer</fen> is aware of.
The category whose applicability to the <fen>Content</fen> is known.
The time when the <fen>Cognizer</fen> has awareness (or lack thereof) of the <fen>Content</fen>.

The <fen>Cognizer</fen> is the person whose awareness of phenomena is at question. With a target verb or adjective the <fen>Cognizer</fen> is generally expressed as an External Argument with the <fen>Content</fen> expressed as an Object or Complement.
The <fen>Content</fen> is the object of the <fen>Cognizer</fen>'s awareness. <fen>Content</fen> can be expressed as a direct object or in a PP Complement.
Some verbs in this frame allow a <fen>Topic</fen> to be expressed in about-PPs.
<fen>Expressor</fen> is the body part that reveals the <fen>Cognizer</fen>'s state to the observer.
The time interval during which the <fen>Cognizer</fen> is aware of the <fen>Content</fen>.
<fen>Speaker</fen>, the person who encodes the <fen>Message</fen>, occurs as the External Argument of all the verbs:
The <fen>Message</fen> is almost invariably expressed in an NP Object. (The only exceptions occur with the verb <t>express</t>, which is occasionally used with that-clause complements.)

For most of the words in this frame, some expression of <fen>Manner</fen> or <fen>Medium</fen> is obligatory. As in other frames, <fen>Manner</fen> expressions characterize the action (in this case, the speech act performed by the <fen>Speaker</fen>). However, a wide range of <fen>Manner</fen> expressions occurs in this frame, including the following types:
<fen>Medium</fen> expresses the <fen>Medium</fen> of communication, such as the language used or the specific type of text in which the <fen>Message</fen> occurs:
listRoleExamples: <fex>Rain</fex> is fairly unlikely today, I think.
There is a high chance of rain <fex>today</fex>.
There is a high chance of rain <fex>in Seattle</fex>.
<fex>He</fex> finds it hard to communicate with people, not least his separated parents .
How do you communicate to them <fex>that you really like them</fex> ?
Had someone communicated to the capital <fex>about the flagrant disregard of the religious law</fex> ?
Opinions are usually communicated <fex>over the telephone</fex> and are often given within 24 hours.
<fex>That most of them are dangerous</fex> is not yet known.
The patient arrived with a suspected <fex>broken leg</fex>.
The <fex>long</fex> suspected killer has now released a statement outlining his thoughts on the criminal case.
<fex>Your boss</fex> is aware of your commitment.
Your boss is aware <fex>of your commitment</fex>.

Yet there is no evidence that Mr. Parrish was cognizant <fex>at the time of the signing
of the notes</fex> that the clauses in issue were present.
The Prime Minister expressed <fex>her sympathy for the victims</fex>.
True Manner: You should phrase it <fex>carefully</fex>.
